Package protoniface

import "github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go/service/proton/protoniface"
Overview
Index

Overview ▹

Overview ▾

Package protoniface provides an interface to enable mocking the AWS Proton service client for testing your code.

It is important to note that this interface will have breaking changes when the service model is updated and adds new API operations, paginators, and waiters.

type ProtonAPI

Package files

interface.go

type ProtonAPI ¶

ProtonAPI provides an interface to enable mocking the proton.Proton service client's API operation, paginators, and waiters. This make unit testing your code that calls out to the SDK's service client's calls easier.

The best way to use this interface is so the SDK's service client's calls can be stubbed out for unit testing your code with the SDK without needing to inject custom request handlers into the SDK's request pipeline. 

// myFunc uses an SDK service client to make a request to
// AWS Proton.
func myFunc(svc protoniface.ProtonAPI) bool {
    // Make svc.AcceptEnvironmentAccountConnection request
}

func main() {
    sess := session.New()
    svc := proton.New(sess)

    myFunc(svc)
}

In your _test.go file: 

// Define a mock struct to be used in your unit tests of myFunc.
type mockProtonClient struct {
    protoniface.ProtonAPI
}
func (m *mockProtonClient) AcceptEnvironmentAccountConnection(input *proton.AcceptEnvironmentAccountConnectionInput) (*proton.AcceptEnvironmentAccountConnectionOutput, error) {
    // mock response/functionality
}

func TestMyFunc(t *testing.T) {
    // Setup Test
    mockSvc := &mockProtonClient{}

    myfunc(mockSvc)

    // Verify myFunc's functionality
}

It is important to note that this interface will have breaking changes when the service model is updated and adds new API operations, paginators, and waiters. Its suggested to use the pattern above for testing, or using tooling to generate mocks to satisfy the interfaces.
